<p>France<br/>Sunday 4.3.1917<br/>My dear Father &amp; Mother,</p>
<p>Another week has gone rather more quickly as we have been on the move, and are now in billets about 20 miles behind the line.</p>
<p>We came here on the 28th doing the trek in one day. Our horses were rather done up but have now recovered well being under cover and on good rations.</p>
<p>We are not doing very much here except a little drill to brighten the show up a bit. Had</p>
